                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d453">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1095</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gonzales</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-16T11:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1917—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President published proclamation this morning guaranteeing security for all
                    pacific citizens whatever their ideas, antecedents and political affiliations so
                    long as they respect the laws. It is a brief appeal intended to bring from
                    hiding, timid persons who do not wish to revolt.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
